Now on github:

   https://github.com/colgreen/sharpneat

The sourceforge SVN repo is still present but the github one will be
the new home.

Recent changes available on the master and V3 branches:

 - Visual Studio solution file updated to 2015 format.
 - Projects updated to target .Net 4.6.1
 - External dependencies being met with nuget packages. Log4net,
ZedGraph and my own new Redzen library which contains general purpose
code previously part of SharpNeat that is now separated out into a new
library (with it's own github repo and nuget package).

There's also a dependency on Box2DX (2D physics engine); that project
was on google code and appears to have been abandoned so I may try and
build it and nugetize it. I'm also open to suggestions for alternative
2D engine options if you think there's something better out there.

Cheers,

Colin
